---
import ApiCopyButton from "../components/ApiCopyButton.astro";
import ApiPanel from "../components/ApiPanel.astro";
import {
  API_PAGES,
  API_SUCCESSFUL_PATH,
  CURL_DISPLAY,
  SMOKE_TO_TERMINAL_DISPLAY,
  apiPageHref,
} from "../model.ts";

/* Each path step opens a section that owns a palette in API_PAGES; the step
   index carries that palette so the path previews the pages it leads to. */
const paletteByHref = new Map(API_PAGES.map((page) => [apiPageHref(page.slug), page.palette]));

const pathMarkdown = API_SUCCESSFUL_PATH.map(
  (step, index) => `${index + 1}. ${step.label} (${step.href}): ${step.detail}`,
).join("\n");

const markdown = `# API Reference

A local HTTP API for evidence-backed media understanding. Register a source, run a bounded study, and read receipts your pipeline can verify. Studio and agentic editors are clients of the same local runtime host; this is not a hosted service.

## Core flow

Endpoints in the order a study uses them:

${pathMarkdown}

An empty list is a valid response, not an error. When the host cannot verify a fact, reads return unavailable or withheld instead of a guess.

## First request

With a running host and bearer token, \`GET /v1/source-sessions\` verifies authorization and lists registered sources.

\`\`\`bash
${CURL_DISPLAY}
\`\`\`

## Quickstart

The smallest sequence that proves the default host end to end: list sources, plan, start, poll events to terminal.

\`\`\`bash
${SMOKE_TO_TERMINAL_DISPLAY}
\`\`\`
`;
---

<header class="api-hero">
  <div class="api-page-header-row">
    <h1>API Reference</h1>
    <ApiCopyButton kind="page" label="Copy page" ariaLabel="Copy page as Markdown" />
  </div>
  <p class="api-lede">
    A local HTTP API for evidence-backed media understanding. Register a source, run a bounded
    study, and read receipts your pipeline can verify. Studio and agentic editors are clients of
    the same local runtime host.
  </p>
  <script is:inline type="application/json" data-api-copy-source set:html={JSON.stringify(markdown)} />
</header>

<section class="api-section" aria-labelledby="api-path-heading">
  <h2 id="api-path-heading">Core Flow</h2>
  <ol class="api-steps">
    {API_SUCCESSFUL_PATH.map((step, index) => (
      <li data-palette={paletteByHref.get(step.href)}>
        <span class="api-step-index" aria-hidden="true">
          {String(index + 1).padStart(2, "0")}
        </span>
        <a href={step.href}>{step.label}</a>
        <span class="api-step-detail">{`: ${step.detail}`}</span>
      </li>
    ))}
  </ol>
  <p>
    An empty list is a valid response, not an error. When the host cannot verify a fact, reads
    return unavailable or withheld instead of a guess. <a href="/api/improve/">Improve</a> documents
    the evaluation loop behind the API; it is not a <code>/v1</code> route.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="api-section" aria-labelledby="api-first-call-heading">
  <h2 id="api-first-call-heading">First Request</h2>
  <div class="api-split">
    <div>
      <p>
        With a running host and bearer token, <code>GET /v1/source-sessions</code> verifies
        authorization and lists registered sources. From there, <a href="/api/runtime/">Runtime
        Lifecycle</a> runs the study itself.
      </p>
      <p>
        The host serves loopback only and requires a bearer token; see <a
        href="/api/authentication/">Authentication</a>. Example responses in this reference were
        captured from a running host; hand-written examples are marked illustrative.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="api-panels">
      <ApiPanel title="Request" body={CURL_DISPLAY} />
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="api-section" aria-labelledby="api-smoke-heading">
  <h2 id="api-smoke-heading">Quickstart</h2>
  <div class="api-split">
    <div>
      <p>
        The smallest sequence that proves the default <code>npm run runtime:host</code> end to
        end: list sources, plan, start, poll events to terminal. No model spend and no hosted
        upload.
      </p>
      <p>
        Caption production comes later, and only after <a href="/api/review/">Publish
        Review</a>. Responses labeled test executor or OpenAI executor require opt-in host flags
        and are not default behavior.
      </p>
    </div>
    {/* The quickstart is Runtime Lifecycle's plan→start→poll loop, so the
        panel wears that page's palette. */}
    <div class="api-panels" data-palette={paletteByHref.get("/api/runtime/")}>
      <ApiPanel title="Quickstart" body={SMOKE_TO_TERMINAL_DISPLAY} />
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
